  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX spot at 7033.7 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7030, dealers are likely hedging neutrally but ready to sell any push higher into the massive +15.8B gamma wall at 7030. The PIN regime with 131B total GEX creates a strong stabilizing environment where dealers will aggressively sell rallies above 7030 and buy dips toward 7015, effectively capping upside momentum. Watch for rejection at the 7030-7035 gamma walls (+15.8B and +15.1B respectively) and support formation around 7015 where dealers flip to buying mode.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy action between 7015-7030 with upside capped by massive gamma walls.",
